Text:
Did you know that π can be used for other things besides math? 

It’s true—there have even been ways of using π  for 🎵  and even 🖼️

Why do we love π?

Jim Bray, chief scientist at GE Global Research says, “This number is not just interesting, but it’s also very important. Many of the engineering formulas that we use to design jet engines or turbines for generating electricity contain π.”

☝️ First things first ☝️

What is π? 

π is the world’s most famous irrational number. This ratio between the circumference and the diameter of a circle is always the same — we generally round it to 3.14, which is why Pi Day falls on March 14.

Happy #NationalPiDay! 

We’re excited to geek out on all things π related. (sorry, not the dessert).
